cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with face recognition using convolutional neural networks and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia), and the use of LSTM networks, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for face recognition, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
